<Algorithm code="           1. Assert: _xBytes_ and _yBytes_ have the same number of elements.           1. Let _result_ be a new empty List.           1. Let _i_ be 0.           1. For each element _xByte_ of _xBytes_, do             1. Let _yByte_ be _yBytes_[_i_].             1. If _op_ is `&amp;`, then               1. Let _resultByte_ be the result of applying the bitwise AND operation to _xByte_ and _yByte_.             1. Else if _op_ is `^`, then               1. Let _resultByte_ be the result of applying the bitwise exclusive OR (XOR) operation to _xByte_ and _yByte_.             1. Else,               1. Assert: _op_ is `|`.               1. Let _resultByte_ be the result of applying the bitwise inclusive OR operation to _xByte_ and _yByte_.             1. Set _i_ to _i_ + 1.             1. Append _resultByte_ to _result_.           1. Return _result_.         ">
